&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit dynamic and focused applicants to the exciting post of Senior clinical fellow in Obstetrics for Private Care with special interest in Fetal Medicine. Two posts are available and will be based predominantly at Chelsea and Westminster site and is a joint venture between NHS and private services. The remit of the post holder is to provide a high quality obstetric service to our population and to support the work of the private patient’s directorate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelsea and Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust comprises two main hospital sites, the Chelsea and Westminster Hospital site in the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea and the West Middlesex University Hospital site in the London Borough of Hounslow. We have a range of other services available in community settings, including our award winning HIV and sexual health centres. With over 5,000 staff caring for nearly one million people locally, regionally, nationally and internationally, we provide a range of specialist clinical services as well as general hospital services, which include A&amp;E and maternity at both our hospital sites. Our ambition is to provide world class patient focused care. We are driven by a desire for excellence in research and a culture of innovation to deliver the latest treatments most efficiently to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post of Senior clinical fellow is full time. Full job description including details of the post available is attached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Miss Charlotte Deans, Consultant Obstetrician: Charlotte.Deans@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
